Paratorna pteropolia is a species of moth of the family Tortricidae. It is found in China (Sichuan).
The wingspan is about 13â€“14.6 mm. The forewings are greyish white from the costa to the apex, but the termen and dorsum are brown. There is a brown spot at the middle of the costa and another at the end of the discal cell. The hindwings are greyish white with a brown costa and apex.